reviews.text: The decoration is contemporary and stylish. Table arrangement is not too spacious. Food is of Chinese cuisine and dim sum, staff are friendly and attentive. The food is averaged and the presentation is excellent, however, it's pricey for lunch and lot more for dinner too. The Yan Toh  Heen restaurant is located at the Intercontinental Hotel Hong Kong with a great view to the Victoria Harbour and also to a section of Avenue of Stars.

Been there last year. 

Love the mellow, rounded, and subtle flavour. Double boiled soup was extraordinary. The food was not oily which suited my preference. 

The service and atmosphere was excellent.
Delicious food,  lovely sea view, polite staff, clean, price of food a bit high, but still full house.  Some credit card has promotion and they will give you some discount

I like the intercontinental hotel, its view on the Victoria Harbour, this restaurant is offer the same view,  the food is delicious, the Peking Duck, the crab and taro croquette. And the service is good.
Very good service and food quality

reviews.text: Best hotel stayed at - club service/atmosphere/view!  Had amazing room with patio and direct view of light show every night!!  Room refresh included private patio refresh/lounge and night lights. Everything was first rate. Service was excellent. Will definitely go back.
Place is dated, rooms are small. Location is good but so much construction. Upgrade planned will be a welcome change. Staff is excellent. 5 star is a stretch. Should be 4.
Very nice lounge and continental breakfast. Workers are quite nice and often offer up their help. Rooms and pool are well kept and has a great view overlooking the sea.

In spite of some renewal in progress, I am very satisfied about my stay, the customer service is excellent and the location is very nice, Tsim Sha Tsui has a lot to offer in the night. The room was certainly five star for me. The view on Victoria Bay is 7 stars for me.

Awesome hotel. Got the harbor view for our honeymoon and it was amazing looking at the downtown skyline of Hong Kong. Also the complementary cellphone was immensely helpful in getting around. Service was exceptional with special recognition going out to Kevin on floor 10 who made sure we always had fresh towels and enough water.

記得要先訂位，人還滿多的。
